From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Keyur Maru <kd2maru@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 13 Jul 2026 04:58:45 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] hidl: allow android.frameworks.displayservice@1.0 in the AOSP
 allowlist

The channel port restores the android.frameworks.displayservice@1.0 HIDL
interface (see the frameworks/hardware/interfaces patch) because the proprietary
camera.msm8953 blob has a hard DT_NEEDED on the 32-bit @1.0 .so. AOSP removed
that interface from allAospHidlInterfaces (upstream 'No displayservice.'), so
hidlInterfaceMutator's canInterfaceExist() rejects the restored module with
'No more HIDL interfaces can be added to Android.' Re-add it to the allowlist so
the interface builds. Pairs with the frameworks/hardware/interfaces restore.
---
 build/hidl_interface.go | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/build/hidl_interface.go b/build/hidl_interface.go
index b517e84..47c4432 100644
--- a/build/hidl_interface.go
+++ b/build/hidl_interface.go
@@ -898,6 +898,7 @@ var allAospHidlInterfaces = map[string]bool{
 	"android.frameworks.cameraservice.service@2.0": true,
 	"android.frameworks.cameraservice.service@2.1": true,
 	"android.frameworks.cameraservice.service@2.2": true,
+	"android.frameworks.displayservice@1.0":        true,
 	"android.frameworks.sensorservice@1.0":         true,
 	"android.frameworks.stats@1.0":                 true,
 	"android.frameworks.vr.composer@1.0":           true,
